Search Bar

 

The main menu of ConservationSpace provides a search bar. The search bar enables you with quick access to search options The search bar contains a few filters:

Search bar gives different search options.

1. You can filter by an object type by clicking on the drop down menu - All

2. You can filter the search by choosing a Context by clicking on the Select Context button and choosing from the dialog window

All search results will be presented in Basic Search screen

3. You can choose a preset Save Search by choosing from the list or to open the Advanced or External Search

To search by keywords use the Enter search terms field. This Search option allows you to search by keywords in some basic fields of the system objects, e.g. title, description, content, etc..
